Ingredients:1kg mixed dried cake fruit200g glac cherries250ml (1 cup) port or dry sherry150ml orange juice45ml (3 tbsp) black treacle250ml (1 cup) brandy250g butter250g soft brown sugar5 extra-large eggs360g (3 cups) cake flour7.5ml (1 tsp) baking powder10ml (2 tsp) mixed spice5ml (1 tsp) ground cinnamon5ml (1 tsp) ground ginger2.5ml ( tsp) ground cloves100g pecan nuts, chopped100g whole peeled almondsWholewheat carrot & fig cake with maple syrup frostingMethod:1) Combine the cake fruit and cherries in a large pan with the port, orange juice, treacle and half the brandy. Bring to the boil, then simmer uncovered for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat, cover with a cloth and set aside overnight to infuse.2) Next day, preheat the oven to 140 C. Line the base and sides of a 23cm cake pan with baking paper.3) In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar together. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift in the flour, baking powder and spices, then add the cooled fruit mixture and the nuts.4) Spoon into the cake pan and bake for 3-4 hours. Allow to cool for 15 minutes in the pan before turning out.5) Warm the remaining brandy, pour over the cake and allow to cool completely before wrapping and storing in an airtight container. Decorate as desired.